655 def test_timid(self): 3.10.macos-latest.c3.10.macos-latest.py3.10.ubuntu-latest.c3.10.ubuntu-latest.py3.10.windows-latest.c3.10.windows-latest.py3.8.macos-latest.c3.8.macos-latest.py3.8.ubuntu-latest.c3.8.ubuntu-latest.py3.8.windows-latest.c3.8.windows-latest.py3.9.macos-latest.c3.9.macos-latest.py3.9.ubuntu-latest.c3.9.ubuntu-latest.py3.9.windows-latest.c3.9.windows-latest.py

656 # Test that the --timid command line argument properly swaps the tracer 

657 # function for a simpler one. 

658 # 

659 # This is complicated by the fact that the tests are run twice for each 

660 # version: once with a compiled C-based trace function, and once without 

661 # it, to also test the Python trace function. So this test has to examine 

662 # an environment variable set in igor.py to know whether to expect to see 

663 # the C trace function or not. 

664 

665 self.make_file("showtrace.py", """\ 

666 # Show the current frame's trace function, so that we can test what the 

667 # command-line options do to the trace function used. 

668 

669 import sys 

670 

671 # Show what the trace function is. If a C-based function is used, then f_trace 

672 # may be None. 

673 trace_fn = sys._getframe(0).f_trace 

674 if trace_fn is None: 

675 trace_name = "None" 

676 else: 

677 # Get the name of the tracer class. Py3k has a different way to get it. 

678 try: 

679 trace_name = trace_fn.im_class.__name__ 

680 except AttributeError: 

681 try: 

682 trace_name = trace_fn.__self__.__class__.__name__ 

683 except AttributeError: 

684 # A C-based function could also manifest as an f_trace value 

685 # which doesn't have im_class or __self__. 

686 trace_name = trace_fn.__class__.__name__ 

687 

688 print(trace_name) 

689 """) 

690 

691 # When running without coverage, no trace function 

692 py_out = self.run_command("python showtrace.py") 

693 assert py_out == "None\n" 

694 

695 cov_out = self.run_command("coverage run showtrace.py") 

696 if os.environ.get('COVERAGE_TEST_TRACER', 'c') == 'c': 

697 # If the C trace function is being tested, then regular running should have 

698 # the C function, which registers itself as f_trace. 

699 assert cov_out == "CTracer\n" 

700 else: 

701 # If the Python trace function is being tested, then regular running will 

702 # also show the Python function. 

703 assert cov_out == "PyTracer\n" 

704 

705 # When running timidly, the trace function is always Python. 

706 timid_out = self.run_command("coverage run --timid showtrace.py") 

707 assert timid_out == "PyTracer\n" 

708
